250 g Ground Lamb
2 unit Artisan Bun
¼ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
1 tbsp Italian Seasoning
½ cup Marinara Sauce
113 g Grape Tomatoes
1 tbsp Balsamic Vinegar
½ tsp Sugar*
2.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt and Pepper*
0.13 tsp Salt*
¼ cup Italian Breadcrumbs
6 g Garlic
56 g Spring Mix

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F. Wash and dry all produce.Line a baking sheet with parchment paper before you begin. It helps get the lamb in the oven quicker! Peel, then mince the garlic. Combine lamb, garlic, Italian seasoning, Italian breadcrumbs, 1/4 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper (dbl both for 4 ppl) in a large bowl. Form mixture into two 4-inch wide patties (four patties for 4 ppl). Lightly press a thumb print into each patty. (NOTE: Don't push all the way through!)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then the patties. Pan-fry, until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side. Remove the pan from heat. Transfer patties to a parchment-lined baking sheet. (TIP: Don't overcrowd the pan, cook the burgers in 2 batches for 4 ppl.)

Spoon marinara sauce evenly over each patty, then sprinkle with cheese. Bake in the bottom of the oven, until patties are cooked through and cheese is melted, 6-8 min.\*\*

While patties cook, halve buns, then arrange them cut-side up on another baking sheet. Toast, in the middle of the oven, until buns are golden-brown, 5-6 min. (NOTE: Keep an eye on them so they do not burn!)

While buns toast, halve tomatoes. Whisk together vinegar, 1/2 tsp sugar and 2 tbsp oil (dbl both for 4 ppl) in another large bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Add spring mix and tomatoes, then toss together.

Place patties between toasted buns. Divide lamb burgers and salad between plates.